0–Male":"1560–Overleden","1590–1665":"1590–1665","1549–1615":"1549–1615","about 1590":"circa 1590","1569":"1569","1665":"1665","1565":"1565","1585":"1585","Cir 1565":"1565","1571":"1571","1560":"1560","1590":"1590","1615":"1615","1549":"1549","England":"England"},"en":{"Cir 1565–":"1565–Deceased","1565–Female":"1565–Deceased","1560–Male":"1560–Deceased","1590–1665":"1590–1665","1549–1615":"1549–1615","about 1590":"about 1590","1569":"1569","1665":"1665","1565":"1565","1585":"1585","Cir 1565":"1565","1571":"1571","1560":"1560","1590":"1590","1615":"1615","1549":"1549","England":"England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Biewett","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English and Irish (of Norman origin): nickname from Old French <i>bleuet</i>, <i>blouet</i> ‘bluish’, a diminutive of <i>bleu</i> ‘blue’, more specifically ‘pale, pallid, wan’, or ‘fair-haired, golden-haired’. Compare   Blew  ,   Blewitt  , and   Bluett  .","History: The Norman Ralph Bloet is mentioned in Domesday Book (1086) as lord of the manor of Hinton in Hampshire, recorded in 1246 as <i>Henton Bluet</i> (modern Hinton Blewett). From the late 12th century onward many Anglo-Norman knights acquired estates in Ireland. Ralph's presumed descendants, Thomas and Ralph Bluet, held lands in counties Cork and Limerick before and after 1254, and are ancestors of the modern Irish families named Bluett, Blewett, and Blewitt. In 1850, following the Irish Potato Famine in Ireland (1845–49), Patrick Blewitt, a son of Edward Blewitt of Ballina, County Mayo, migrated to North America, his whole family joining him in 1851 to settle in Scranton PA. Joe Biden (see   Biden  ), the 46th president of the US, is Edward's great-great-great grandson."],"variants":[{"name":"Blewitt","meanings":["English: variant of   Blewett  ."]},{"name":"Bluett","meanings":["English (Cornwall): variant of   Blewett  ."]},{"name":"Blew","meanings":["Americanized form of German and Jewish (Ashkenazic)   Blau   ‘blue’. Compare   Blue  .","English: from Middle English <i>blew(e)</i>, a variant of <i>bleu</i> ‘blue’ (Old French <i>bleu</i>), ‘pale, pallid, wan’ (of complexion), or ‘fair, golden’ (of hair). Compare   Blewett  ."]},{"name":"Biden","meanings":["English (Hampshire and Surrey): habitational name, probably from Baydon (Wiltshire). The placename may have meant ‘hill associated with a woman named Bēage’ (a personal name derived from Old English <i>bēag</i> ‘ring, bracelet, torque’ + Old English <i>dūn</i>). The surname is pronounced /'baidən/.","History: The surname <i>Biden</i> has a long history in East Meon (Hampshire), recorded there from 1327 until at least the 1840s. — Joe Biden, the 46th president of the US, is of Irish, English, and French descent. His mother’s Jean (Catherine Eugenia) Finnegan entire family tree traces back to Ireland, with some of the ancestors named Blewitt (see   Blewett  )."]},{"name":"Bluitt","meanings":["English (of Norman origin): variant of   Blewett  . This surname is now rare in Britain."]}]},{"name":"Maria","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Maria  , of German origin but now also moderately popular in the English-speaking world."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705205,"age":4,"year":"1569","julianDay":2294126,"title":"State Lottery","description":"A State Lottery was recorded in 1569. The tickets were sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705206,"age":6,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705207,"age":20,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Maria “Mary” Biewett was born in 1565, in England as the daughter of Richard Bluett. She had at least 1 son with Digery Dickery Carwithen."},"et":{"Cir 1565–":"1565–Surnud","1565–Female":"1565–Surnud","1560–Male":"1560–Surnud","1590–1665":"1590–1665","1549–1615":"1549–1615","about 1590":"umbes 1590","1569":"1569","1665":"1665","1565":"1565","1585":"1585","Cir 1565":"1565","1571":"1571","1560":"1560","1590":"1590","1615":"1615","1549":"1549","England":"England"},"fi":{"Cir 1565–":"1565–Kuollut","1565–Female":"1565–Kuollut","1560–Male":"1560–Kuollut","1590–1665":"1590–1665","1549–1615":"1549–1615","about 1590":"noin 1590","1569":"1569","1665":"1665","1565":"1565","1585":"1585","Cir 1565":"1565","1571":"1571","1560":"1560","1590":"1590","1615":"1615","1549":"1549","England":"England"},"fr":{"Cir 1565–":"1565–Décédée","1565–Female":"1565–Décédée","1560–Male":"1560–Décédé","1590–1665":"1590–1665","1549–1615":"1549–1615","about 1590":"environ 1590","1569":"1569","1665":"1665","1565":"1565","1585":"1585","Cir 1565":"1565","1571":"1571","1560":"1560","1590":"1590","1615":"1615","1549":"1549","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Maria “Mary” Biewett est née en 1565, à Angleterre, fille de Richard Bluett. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Digery Dickery Carwithen."},"de":{"Cir 1565–":"1565–Verstorben","1565–Female":"1565–Verstorben","1560–Male":"1560–Verstorben","1590–1665":"1590–1665","1549–1615":"1549–1615","about 1590":"um 1590","1569":"1569","1665":"1665","1565":"1565","1585":"1585","Cir 1565":"1565","1571":"1571","1560":"1560","1590":"1590","1615":"1615","1549":"1549","England":"England","lifeSummary":"Maria “Mary” Biewett wurde 1565 in England, als Tochter von Richard Bluett geboren. Sie hatte mit Digery Dickery Carwithen mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"Cir 1565–":"1565–Desede","1565–Female":"1565–Desede","1560–